thread.title_full: Test-driving a Project Fi phone: it works, even in BART tunnels - San Francisco Chronicle

author: Benny Evangelista
title: Test-driving a Project Fi phone: it works, even in BART tunnels
text: Google’s Project Fi — which turns the search giant into a mobile phone carrier — promises an intriguingly simple monthly mobile plan: $20 for talk and text, $10 for every GB of data, and it automatically selects the fastest speeds among two different carriers and Wi-Fi networks.
